    <summary type="text" />
    <g-custom:tags type="string" />
    <media:content medium="image" url="https://irp-cdn.multiscreensite.com/md/unsplash/dms3rep/multi/photo-1498811008858-d95a730b2ffc.jpg" />
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <title>SOME TIPS AND THOUGHT-PROVOKING COMMENTS FOR THE RSA BUSINESS ENVIRONMENT.</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="http://www.themarketintellect.co.za/some-tips-and-thought-provoking-comments-for-the-rsa-business-environment" />
    <author>
      <name />
    </author>
    <updated>2020-04-19T20:34:50Z</updated>
    <published>2020-04-19T20:34:50Z</published>
    <content>&lt;h3 style="transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out 0s;"&gt;&#xD;
  
                  
         PEOPLE HAVE CHANGED THEIR BEHAVIOUR AND ROUTINES AND THESE CHANGES ARE HERE TO STAY.
        
                &#xD;
&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;img src="https://irp-cdn.multiscreensite.com/md/unsplash/dms3rep/multi/photo-1500068939895-dd5d4be36e7e.jpg"/&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;h3 style="transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out 0s;"&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;span style=""&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          IT IS STRIKING TO NOTE THAT ON THE LAST DAY OF THE ORIGINAL LOCKDOWN THAT PEOPLE HAS FLOCKED TO TOWN TO DO SHOPPING. EVEN HANDYMEN WITH LDV LOADS OF WORKERS AND MATERIAL WERE ON THE ROADS.
          
                    &#xD;
    &lt;span&gt;&#xD;
      
                      
            
          
                    &#xD;
    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div style="transition: none 0s ease 0s; display: block;" data-rss-type="text"&gt;&#xD;
  
                  
         BELOW FOLLOWS SOME HINTS AND FACTS THAT CAN HELP BUSINESSES TO ADJUST THEIR STRATEGY AND BUSINESS PLANS. 
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;b style=""&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            The 
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             Core business no longer a holy cow.
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            Many businesses have experienced implosions of their production and/or supply of services, or even the deferring of deliveries. The only cure for this distress is to adapt. 
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            The positive side is that FAO has published its Food Price index which shows that world food prices are declining.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            FIFO!
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            This adaption is discussed below. 
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            There are long-term incentives to making
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;b&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             sanitisers and face masks
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            . Global leading companies are switching away from their core business to manufacture these products. Some companies are in a position to “slip in” these processes into their normal operations. 
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             Examples of such companies are Sasol (petrochemical). Also, Fonterra, Danone, Beingmate which are all dairy companies.
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;b&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             Transport
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            in the UK has dropped by 67% during the lockdown. The same is expected in the RSA. Transport businesses and their clients must look for other alternatives. 
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          &lt;b&gt;&#xD;
            
                            
              Car sales
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             in the EU have plunged by 55,1% during lockdown. I am sure that the car manufacturers did not see this one coming. 
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             There also the
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;b&gt;&#xD;
            
                            
              alcohol
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             beverage companies that are
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;i&gt;&#xD;
            
                            
              switching their resources to manufacture non-alcoholic beverages
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;/i&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             . Non-alcoholic sales are up 58% y-o-y in the Western world. “1 in 5 prefer non-alcoholic drinks.”  
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             There will be a major shift to “grown up” simple
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;b&gt;&#xD;
            
                            
              soft drinks
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             . 
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             The
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;i&gt;&#xD;
            
                            
              e-commerce sale of alcohol and fresh foods
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;/i&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             has surged in China during the COVID-19 pandemic. These changes are predicted to stay. Hence the impact on retailers and stores will be significant. 
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             The
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;b&gt;&#xD;
            
                            
              digital economy
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             has arrived, forcing businesses, e.g. retailers to shift towards client attracting vs waiting for clients to do business with them. Businesses have not viewed online shopping as important, as only 1,4% of South Africans were buying online. That is before the Virus. 
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            The lockdown has exposed the fragility of people’s access to essential goods and services. It is also likely that the number of people losing income, will grow. 
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          &lt;b&gt;&#xD;
            
                            
              Food shopping procedures
             
                          &#xD;
          &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             must be restructured (a nudge from the state?). More attention should be given to the urban informal settlements with a high population density.
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            As people are staying at home due to the COVID-19 pandemic, restaurants &amp;amp; fast foods are closed, baking at home has become a favourite task. Baking now at home does not only make food for the family, but also relieve boredom. Expect that quarantine at home will boost demand for powdered products. The demand for powdered products has increased by 80% during the COVID-19 outbreak. 
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            Sales of instant and long-life foods like:
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Frozen meals.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Instant noodles.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Processed meats.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Seafood.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Milk.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;span style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);"&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             have surged during the lockdown, especially via e-commerce.  
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            Businesses have now realised that they will have to be more client-attracting, e.g. retailers now offer to deliver same day orders.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            Businesses should plan for a rental war, involving landlords, and their clients. On a larger scale the JSE listed retail giants have offered landlords 20% of their rent, until it is business as usual for everyone involved. The Landlords Association (RLA) made a counter offer of between 15% and 100% temporary discount (interest free) on rentals, including small businesses e.g. restaurants, etc. A few of the examples of the retail giants are:
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Pepkor.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Truworths.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Mr. Price.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	Woolworths.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            Finally: businesses must keep in mind that if they decide to do business online (and have all the technical support) it does not mean that their
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;b&gt;&#xD;
          
                          
             clients will be ready for doing business online
            
                        &#xD;
        &lt;/b&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            :
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	The clients struggle to balance family time with work time.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	The clients do not have the physical environment to do business (some do not have a study, work in the kitchen, in bed,etc.
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            -	The clients do not have the necessary infrastructure to participate, e.g. they have no computer, etc. 
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            REFERENCES:
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            a)	T. Koe, (Dairy reporter, 13/04/20) “Fighting back: Fonterra, Danone, Beigemat join the COVID-19 push for sanitisers, facemasks.”
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            b)	F. Southy, (Beverage Daily, 03/04/20) “Alcohol-free: could CBD help bridge the gap for sceptics?” 
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            c)	F. Southy, (Food Navigator, 15/04/20) “Food insecurity: How Covid-19 is exacerbating a crisis already on a knife-edge basis.”
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            d)	J. Cornall, (Dairy Reporter, 14/04/20) “Quarantine baking boosts demand for powdered goods.”
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            e)	Matt Hancock, (Sky News, 18h15, 15/04/20).
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            f)	S. Naidoo, (Moneyweb, 15/04/20) “Lockdown: JSE-listed retail giants offer landlords a fifth of rent.”
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            g)	G. Yu-Lim, (Beverage Daily.com, 15/04/20) “E-commerce boost for alcohol and fresh food during COVID-19 likely to remain.”
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            h)	C. Ryan, (Economy, Moneyweb, 14/04/20) “The ‘digital’ economy has arrived.”
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            i)	Stone Fox capital (Market place, 13/04/20) “CrowdStrike: Too far, too little.  
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            j)	F. Southy, (Food Navigator, 17/04/20) “Brussels Bulletin: World food prices ‘decline sharply’ in March.”
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div style="text-align: justify;"&gt;&#xD;
        
                        
            k)	Y. Minkoff, (SA News Editor, 17/04/20). “European Car Sales drop most on record.”
           
                      &#xD;
      &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
      &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
        &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
