  <entry>
    <title>HOW TO DO BUSINESS AFTER THE VIRUS</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="http://www.themarketintellect.co.za/how-to-do-business-after-the-virus" />
    <author>
      <name />
    </author>
    <updated>2020-03-29T21:04:27Z</updated>
    <published>2020-03-29T21:04:27Z</published>
    <content>&lt;h3 style="transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out 0s;"&gt;&#xD;
  
                  
         Prepare Yourself For A New Way Of Doing Business
        
                &#xD;
&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;img src="https://irp-cdn.multiscreensite.com/a81d873f/dms3rep/multi/IMG-20200328-WA0016-9baf90f1.jpg"/&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div style="transition: none 0s ease 0s; display: block;" data-rss-type="text"&gt;&#xD;
  
                  
         75 years ago the sliding rule was the top calculator, even scientific wise. It was even faster for the first 20 years than the first calculators. The emergence of the digital age has made sliding rulers immediately obsolete. The manufacturers did not even see it coming. 
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          Our seven scenarios indicate that that is going to happen 'after the Virus'. Be aware, people only change if the change is traumatic, and that change is happening now. Businesses will slowly go out of doing business, even the ones that are comfortably surviving the Virus. This change in doing business will shock people, because 'who would have thought that this would happen'.
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    &lt;br/&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/div&gt;</content>
    <summary type="text" />
    <g-custom:tags type="string" />
    <media:content medium="image" url="https://irp-cdn.multiscreensite.com/a81d873f/dms3rep/multi/IMG-20200328-WA0016.jpg" />
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <title>THE VIRUS: LIFE WILL NEVER BE THE SAME.</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="http://www.themarketintellect.co.za/the-virus-life-will-never-be-the-same" />
    <author>
      <name />
    </author>
    <updated>2020-03-24T08:52:41Z</updated>
    <published>2020-03-24T08:52:41Z</published>
    <content>&lt;h3 style="transition: opacity 1s ease-in-out 0s;"&gt;&#xD;
  
                  
         Face reality
        
                &#xD;
&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;img src="https://irp-cdn.multiscreensite.com/a81d873f/dms3rep/multi/Slide3.PNG"/&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;div style="transition: none 0s ease 0s; display: block;" data-rss-type="text"&gt;&#xD;
  
                  
         We were and are not ready for the TOTAL effect of the Virus.
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          No one knows what our environment will look like this year. And the next
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          decade?
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          Scenario planning is needed, we have done seven different scenarios. We
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          heard that there are already organisations doing scenario strategy planning,
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          Sunter style.
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          The government will not be able to protect us on its own. Businesses will have
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          to take up the slack, whilst they must exist profitably.
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          Business environments are going to change, that’s why we are already
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          planning for new changes. The role of businesses has changed. Communities
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          will expect even more involvement or sacrifices from business leaders. Will
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          investors accept that?
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
  &lt;div&gt;&#xD;
    
                    
          BUSINESSES WIL HAVE TO CHANGE THE WAY THEY DO BUSINESS, FOREVER.
         
                  &#xD;
  &lt;/div&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/div&gt;</content>
